
Three states of a git project:
1.       Working Directory
2.       Staging Area (Index)
3.       .git Directory (Repository)

Below global commands should run when Git is first installed.
git --version (yüklü olduğunu test etmek ve versiyon kontrolü için)
git config --global user.name "Murat Akgul"
git config --global user.mail "muratakgul98@gmail.com"

git config --list (lists all configuration settings for git)

man git (get help for all commands)
git help (get help for all command - short info)
Porcelain commands are important, plumbing commands for detailed stuff in Git
git help config (get help for configuration)

git init -creates an empty git repo for all source codes are exist in the path
git add .  --> index everything in the Git initialized current directory
git commit -m "First commit for my project" --> snapshot everything in the Git initilized current directory
git commit -a -m "second commit" -- > skip the "git add" command and commit directly
git status --> displays in which branch we are on and check whether exist anything to commit
git status --short ya da git status -s --> displays m, a ve ??. m is modified at stage area, a is new added file, ?? İs untracked file

Is there anything missing previous commit or commit message is written wrong, we can go back to previous commit with below command:
git commit --amend
